               <msContents>
                  <summary>The second part of the first volume of the <title>Ḥabīb al-Siyar</title> (Beloved of Biographies) completed by the author 
                     <persName key="person_45109504" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/45109504/" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Ghiyās̲ al-Dīn ibn Humām al-Dīn (ca. 1475–1535)</persName> 
                     known as <addName key="person_45109504" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/45109504/">Khvāndamīr (1487–1524 CE)</addName>, in <date>937 AH (1530–31 CE)</date>.
                     A popular general history covering the pre-Islamic period up to the time of Shāh Ismāʿīl I, the entire work consists of a preface, an introduction, three volumes—each of which contains four sections appended with lists of names of 
                     prominent figures associated with each period—followed by an epilogue. This volume covers This volume opens with the histories of the Persian kings
                     after the creation of Adam up to the prophet of Islam.
                     </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_972-item1">
                     <author key="person_45109504" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/45109504/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Khvānd Mīr, Ghiyās̲ al-Dīn ibn Humām al-Dīn, ca. 1475-1535?</persName><lb/>
